Re: What's with this odd generation?

Bitcointalk

2010-02-14 15:52:23 UTC - [11]Original Post

   Right.  Otherwise we couldnʼt have a finite limit of 21 million coins,
   because there would always need to be some minimum reward for
   generating.  In a few decades when the reward gets too small, the
   transaction fee will become the main compensation for nodes.  Iʼm sure
   that in 20 years there will either be very large transaction volume or
   no volume.
